Description: network emulation protocol tests
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: InterWorking Labs creates network emulation and protocol testing products to improve the quality and operation of apps and devices in mobile, cloud, and wide area networks.   Our network simulators are used for pre-deployment testing, proof-of-concept demonstrations, and what-if scenarios.  Developers, IT managers and test engineers use InterWorking Labs products to validate both product quality and network operation.   Our clients  include Alcatel-Lucent, Apple,  AT&T, Boeing, Cisco, Ericsson, Hewlett Packard, Intel, Phillips, Siemens, US Army, US Navy, and many more. Our Maxwell family of network emulators  capture and change network flows, inducing the conditions that cause network congestion, slow links, time outs, and many other adverse network conditions.   Network managers can then see the effects on the device or application to find and fix bugs, solve network problems, and learn the limits of device and application performance. Our protocol test tools identify flaws in the implementation of TCP, IPv4, IPv6, DHCP, SNMP, and many more protocols.
